{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Psa|116","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","chapter":116,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":1,"text":"I love the Lord because he has heard my appeal for mercy.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":2,"text":"Because he has turned his ear to me, I will call out to him as long as I live.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":3,"text":"The ropes of death were wrapped around me, and the torments of Sheol overcame me; I encountered trouble and sorrow.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":4,"text":"Then I called on the name of the Lord: “Lord, save me!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":5,"text":"The Lord is gracious and righteous; our God is compassionate.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":6,"text":"The Lord guards the inexperienced; I was helpless, and he saved me.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":7,"text":"Return to your rest, my soul, for the Lord has been good to you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":8,"text":"For you, Lord, rescued me from death, my eyes from tears, my feet from stumbling.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":9,"text":"I will walk before the Lord in the land of the living.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":10,"text":"I believed, even when I said, “I am severely oppressed.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":11,"text":"In my alarm I said, “Everyone is a liar.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":12,"text":"How can I repay the Lord for all the good he has done for me?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":13,"text":"I will take the cup of salvation and call on the name of the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":14,"text":"I will fulfill my vows to the Lord in the presence of all his people.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":15,"text":"The death of his faithful ones is valuable in the Lord’s sight.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:116:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":116,"verse":16,"text":"Lord, I am indeed yo